Below WMI Methods are dependent on the project, skip it if not supported.


Note. All the WMI methods support or not need checked with your RD team. Even the WMI method name has a word X60 or X70, it may also support on Gen 9/10/11, etc. products.


For example, GET_DOLBY_THREE_MODE_C970_VER, GET_GAMELOGO_X60_VER， GET_RGB_KBD_LE_Y560_Y760_VER， and GET_SERVICE_KEY_C970_VER such keys that need special confirmation.

Section : Fn+R Wmi check (30) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
PS:X80 and later models if the machine supports FN+R refresh rate switching function, you need to perform the following tests
1.Click "ReadBIOSRefreshRate" in the WMI Tool.
Check the info: Max/MinmumRefreshRate parameter.
2.Click on "OpenReg show all capability", check the registry "BiosACDCPanelRefreshRateMax/Min" parameter
Record refresh rate parameters
3.Enable path: Win+I→Display→Advanced Display. Check that the maximum and minimum values of the system refresh rate are consistent with the previously recorded values
Keep the values consistent and Fill in the table
